	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_DARDO_IFV888">
			<Text>Dardo IFV</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_DARDO_IFV888_STRATEGY">
			<Text>Light Armor Infantry Fighting Vehicles (IFV) are stronger and faster than regular Infantry. Although fast, Mech Infantry can move after combat like Tanks; their primary responsibility is, hit and run tactics, and anti-tank warfare.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_DARDO_IFV888_HELP">
			<Text>Fast ranged late game unit, it is designed to carry anti-tank missiles, and use hit and run tactics to be effective in battle.  -- They have a range of 1 and can't take cities.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_UNIT_DARDO_IFV888_PEDIA">
			<Text>The Dardo is an infantry fighting vehicle designed for the Italian Army as a replacement for the M113 APC. It is designed and built by the Iveco Fiat Oto Melara Syndicated Company based in Rome. Iveco is responsible for the hull and propulsion systems, while Oto Melara is responsible for the weapons and fire control systems.[NEWLINE]The Dardo is primarily armed with the 25mm Oerlikon KBA automatic cannon firing 600 rounds per minute, with 200 rounds of ready to fire ammunition stored in the turret . Two 7.62mm NATO machine guns are also installed in the turret, one coaxially mounted with the main gun. Five rifle ports, two on each side of the hull and one in the rear are provided to allow troops inside to use their personal weapons, if needed.[NEWLINE]Fire control is provided by the Galileo Avionica Hitfist integrated fire control system which is capable of measuring target speed and range. The commander is provided with six episcope sights which provides 360° field of view. The cupola can be further fitted with a panoramic stabilised sight. Additionally, a laser range finder and a thermal imager is provided for the gunner. The commander is equipped with a monitor that displays the view from the gunner night vision system.[NEWLINE]For dealing with heavy armoured threats, two Spike-LR anti tank missiles can be installed on both sides of the turret with a maximum range of 4 km. -- Wikipedia</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
